## Full Training Pipeline

```bash
# Stage 1: Pretrain modality encoders independently (5 epochs)
python scripts/train_stage1_encoders.py --config configs/main_config.yaml

# Stage 2: Joint pretraining of CAFL + BSE + demographic head (3 epochs)
python scripts/train_stage2_fusion.py --config configs/main_config.yaml \
    --stage1_checkpoint checkpoints/stage1/

# Stage 3: ECRL policy fine-tuning (Algorithm 1), 5 seeds x 1200 episodes
for seed in 0 1 2 3 4; do
    python scripts/train_stage3_ecrl.py --config configs/main_config.yaml \
        --seed $seed --stage2_checkpoint checkpoints/stage2/ \
        --output_dir results/raw_logs/ecrl_s1/
done
```

Estimated time: ~72 GPU-hours per seed on 4x A100-80GB (Stage 3 dominates).

## Full Evaluation Pipeline

```bash
# Generate the MultiEthic-V benchmark (or download pre-generated logs)
python benchmarks/MultiEthic-V/generate_benchmark.py --seed 42

# Run all 5 baselines + MEIA on the full 12,000-session benchmark
python scripts/run_full_evaluation.py \
    --benchmark_dir benchmarks/MultiEthic-V/generated/ \
    --meia_checkpoint checkpoints/stage3_final/ \
    --output_dir results/raw_logs/eval/

# Generate Table 3 and Figure 3 from the evaluation outputs
python results/tables/make_table3.py --eval_dir results/raw_logs/eval/
python results/figures/make_figure3.py --eval_dir results/raw_logs/eval/
```

## Notes on Reproducibility

- All random seeds are fixed in `configs/main_config.yaml` (`seed: 42`)
  and per-seed training uses seeds 0-4 for the 5-seed average reported
  in Figure 2.
- The GPT-4o baselines (B1, B2) use a pinned snapshot
  (`gpt-4o-2024-08-06`); since commercial endpoints can change behaviour
  over time even for pinned snapshots, the exact prompts and recorded
  outputs are released in `supplementary/B_gpt4o_prompts/` for full
  reproducibility independent of the live API.
- Bootstrap confidence intervals use 1000 iterations with `seed=42`
  (see `src/evaluation/metrics.py::bootstrap_ci`).
